Package: GSignTest
Type: Package
Title: Robust Tests for Regression-Parameters via Sign Depth
Version: 1.0.5
Author: Melanie Horn
Maintainer: Melanie Horn <mhorn@statistik.tu-dortmund.de>
Date: 2020-01-20
Description: The Simplicial Depth is a robust measure of fitness for 
  a regression model. One can use it also for testing whether a given 
  parameter vector of a regression model fits to some data. The Sign 
  Depth needs a sorting of the data, which can be difficult with 
  multivariate data. This package provides different strategies for
  sorting multivariate data (random, nondominated-sorting, sorting 
  via scalarization, shortest hamiltonian path, ...) and calculates 
  robust tests for regression-parameters via Sign Depth.
